runs.comm: that's not a bad way to start! Stirling tossed it down the leg side and Borren went on his knee and swept it in the air down to fine leg
went down the track and checked his shot, the ball drops on the pitch
he goes back and whips it to the leg side
comes down the track and pushes it to the off side
goes back and whips it with the turn to the on side
this was heaved away but mistimed, down on his knee and the ball is in the air and drops at deep midwicket
that went a really long way! Spin from this end as well, he comes down the track and lofts him high over long-on
comes down the track and the ball hits his pads and drops on the pitch
they're looking comfortable against spin! Tossed up on middle and he gets on his knee and slogs him and it drops just over the rope at deep midwicket
same direction and he goes longer! Tossed up and he gets on his knee and slogs him high over deep midwicket
even longer and higher! Myburgh on his knee and he sends it over deep midwicket
goes for the slog but he misses this one, held back the pace
he beats the bat first up as the batsman has a poke at this length delivery outside off
raining sixes here! What a shot this is! He bends down on his knee and laps up the length delivery over deep square leg
dances down the pitch and misses it as the bowler fires it on the pads, they take a leg bye
another boundary! This is a deluge.. everything is hitting the middle. The batsman mows across the line and slaps it to deep square leg
he bowls the slower bouncer and it lobs above the batsman's cross-batted swing, beaten outside off
a good yorker from the bowler this time, it can only be dug out as far as mid on for a single
one more! This is in the arc and it's flat-batted down to the long-on boundary.. There is a fielder there, who moves to his right but has no chance..The 50 is up.. what is it the 4th over!
whoa! This is unbelievable! The batsman goes for a pull, gets a top edge and for a moment, it looks like someone would get under it.. no, this over fine leg
this is massive! What is going on! This is the best of all! Overpitched delivery. It's murdered to the sight screen area
bowls a full and wide delivery outside off from round the wicket.. The batsman misses it this time.. The umpire says it's ok.. could have been a wide on another day
looks to send this to Amstedamn, makes no connection though.. First miss I have seen in a loooong time
full toss wide outside off, invitation to hit, the batsman goes down on his knee and powers it over the infield.. Keep them coming.. It's only a four..
What the!!! This is wide outside off and the batsman drags it to the deep midwicket boundary with a powerful mow!
a very good yorker from Murtaugh! The batsman flicks it fine on the leg side for a single
a very good short ball from Murtaugh, gets it high up on the shoulder.. The batsman swings his bat, but misses the top edge
low full toss on the stumps! That is whacked straight down the ground for another boundary.. That is also Myburgh's fifty.. off only 17 balls
the cover dives to his left, the extra cover dives to his right.. but no one gets a hand to it.. Myburgh slams the low full toss to the boundary again..
looks to slog it to the leg side but misses, they take a leg bye to short third man anyway
he bowls a good yorker from round the stumps, dug out back to the bowler
gets an inside edge on to his pads, then it runs to short third man.. It wasn't too far from the off stump..
good delivery this one! It beats the bat as the batsman makes room and looks to power it through off. The keeper is standing up to the stumps
slower delivery on the pads, breaks the short spell of dots balls as he flicks it over deep backward square leg for an easy boundary
high full toss and that is just punched down the ground.. Mid-off is up, so the batsman just needs to beat him and he does...

what a catch from Dockrell! The manic stand has come to an end. Borren looks to slice it over the infield but ends up getting a thick outside edge. Dockrell runs towards the boundary and pulls off a stunner as the ball was coming from behind him
flatter and quicker, the batsman punches it to wide long on for a single
unstoppable! Only a touch fuller and Muburgh slaps it with awesome power over deep midwicket. It was flat hit, the fielder looked interested for a bit, but it never came down
the fun and games end! he looks for the same region off a shorter delivery but doesn't get hold of it and gets caught at the deep midwicket boundary. What an innings this has been!
slower this time from Dockrell, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
he walks to the off side and works it away to midwicket for a single
slower still from the bowler, the batsman nudges it behind square on the leg side to bring up the team's 100
length delivery on the stumps, no room there.. the batsman pushes it back to the bowler

Ireland are coming back with their fielding! Another cracker of a catch, this time from Porterfield! Van Beek looked to launch the length ball over to the sight screen, but ends up hitting it high.. The mid-off fielder runs with his back towards the batsman and times his dive to perfection to hold on to this.. Stunning catch
pushed calmly down to long on.. this is in stark contrast to what was happening ten minutes ago..
well done by short third man as he dives to his right to cut off the late cut..
length delivery on the pads, it's slightly short too and Barresi swivels to easily find the gap at deep square leg
back of length delivery outside off, punched firmly to long off
slower from Dockrell, forces the batsman to generate all the speed, punched down to long on for  single
oh no! We have jinxed Ireland's fielding here! Barresi reverse sweeps this straight to Joyce at deep cover, who drops a sitter
another misfield at midwicket allows a single now..
tossed up, full, Cooper has come ready for these.. He sends this miles high and miles long over deep midwicket
looks to hammer this across the line, but Dockrell is smartly keeping it slow.. The batsman gets hit on the chest

this is very close! The batsman looked to hit across and gets hit on his chest (he is down on his knee) and it looked like a very good shout, but the umpire reckons that would have gone down leg. Replays show it was hitting leg. Thought so...
so let's start the sixes show again, says Barresi.. Length delivery from round the stumps, it's whacked over deep square leg with utter ease
defends the flatter delivery back to the bowler
moves to the leg side and hammers the flatter delivery down to long off, all along the ground
gimme four gimme five gimme six! Flat batted, swatted, murdered over deep square leg..
premeditated scoop! He waits and waits, then laps it fine on the leg side for a couple of runs..
goes for the reverse pull but misses.. that wasn't far from the off stump.. But they take a single to short third man
what a swipe! Absolutely nothing wrong with the ball.. He stands tall and launches it to deep midiwcket boundary
full, straight, to the sight screen.. What am I doing here!
this is the biggest one ever! Hat-trick again.. Full delivery, hammered over deeepmidwicket.. Dockrell is leaking here.
six more! He gets down on his knees and just helps him along over deep square leg.. This ground is looking very small at the moment.. and it's not small.. trust me
this one is hammered down the pitch.. all along the ground, through the bowler's legs..
he gets an inside edge on to his pads.. This is the highlight
wide length delivery, through the fielder at point.. Another boundary.. who said  Ireland don't misfield!
short delivery, Cooper's cameo comes to an end as he pulls this straight to deep backward square leg.. Relief for Zimbabwe.. No relief for Ireland though.. What an innings this has been from Cooper!
he is beaten by a slower bouncer, the batsman waits and waits, still plays early
what a good ball! In the block hole and Barresi digs it out straight down the ground
he is beaten first ball.. it's been a while since something went past the outside edge like that
this goes high in the night sky as Ben drives it inside out, but drops well inside the boundary.. Not a six..
length ball, swiped to deep midwicket for a single for a change
length delivery, looks to swat it to the leg side but gets beaten..
comes down the track and punches this to long on for a single
yes, they won't mind this.. If they are not coming in front, the edges will also do the job.. This one is a faint nick and slides down to the third man boundary
another swing of the bat, an inside edge takes it to short fine leg
make it 28! Ben gets a length delivery that he murders over deep midwicket.. that has well cleared the boundary. into the stands
a very good short delivery, he chases the batsman as he creates room and manages to get it shoulder high as well.. No contact on that one
he moves leg side and slams this short of length delivery with a powerful down the line winner.. Straight straight straight.. to the sight screeen
a very good yorker again, he can only dig it out to the bowler
fulll toss, clobbered through extra cover for a boundary.. They are almost there.. Netherlands have set the scene on fire..
Massive massive! Netherlands have smashed their way to the next round.. In one swipe, the batsman sends two teams back.. Over deep midwicket
